(nL2TLBWays, power_pad).explanation: The number of ways in L2 TLB affects internal cache organization but has no direct relationship to pad power consumption, which is related to I/O interface power;

(nL2TLBWays, nICacheTLBWays).explanation: These are independent cache design parameters for different cache levels and serve different functions in the memory hierarchy;

(nL2TLBWays, power_switching).explanation: Increasing the number of ways in L2 TLB requires more complex selection logic and multiplexers, which increases switching activity and dynamic power consumption;
